-- Neotel to Add 50,000 Customers by Next Year, Business Day Says
-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 2012-05-23T05:48:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/neotel-to-add-50-000-customers-by-next-year-business-day-says.html
Neotel Ltd., the South African unit
of  India ’s  Tata Communications Ltd. (TCOM) , plans to add 50,000
customers by the end of its 2013 fiscal year and will spend 500
million rand ($60 million) expanding its infrastructure this
year, Business Day reported, citing Chief Executive Officer
Sunil Joshi.  The company reported “positive” earnings before interest,
tax, depreciation and amortization for the year through March
for the first time since its introduction five years ago, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
 sgunnion@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
